This paper presents a novel algorithm for evaluating hex-programs, which are a type of nonmonotonic logic programs that allow for bidirectional communication with external sources of computation. The paper focuses on conflict-driven ASP solving techniques, which are commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for solving logic programs. Additionally, the paper discusses learning techniques, which are also commonly used in AI and machine learning (cs.LO). The use of external sources of computation also relates to natural language processing (cs.CL) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the algorithm, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE).
